<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14406] Double iteration of records in batches to be restored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14406</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While restoring a batch of records,&#160;&lt;tt&gt;RocksDBStore&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;was iterating the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;ConsumerRecord&lt;/tt&gt;s, building a list of&#160;&lt;tt&gt;KeyValue&lt;/tt&gt;s, and then iterating&#160;&lt;em&gt;that&lt;/em&gt;&#160;list of&#160;&lt;tt&gt;KeyValue&lt;/tt&gt;s to add them to the RocksDB batch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simply adding the key and value directly to the RocksDB batch prevents this unnecessary second iteration, and the creation of itermediate&#160;&lt;tt&gt;KeyValue&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;objects, improving the performance of state restoration, and reducing unnecessary object allocation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(thanks to Nick Telford for finding this)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
